HEADWORD: Observantine
<hw>Ob`ser*van"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Fr.
<ets>observantin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>One of a
branch of the <org>Order of Franciscans</org>, who profess to adhere
more strictly than the Conventuals to the intention of the founder,
especially as to poverty; -- called also
<altname>Observants</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

